FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778505069
OL,3,CBirmingham MP says Starmer must go as
OL,4,CPM fights off leadership pressure
OL,6,FIn a strongly worded statement,
OL,7,FHamilton said: "The people of the
OL,8,FUnited Kingdom have spoken, and the
OL,9,Ftransition must now be orderly and
OL,10,Frespectful of their verdict.
OL,12,F"In my view, the public have made it
OL,13,Fclear that they do not wish to hear
OL,14,Ffurther talk of a 'reset' from Sir
OL,15,FKeir Starmer. Confidence has been
OL,16,Flost, and voters have stopped
OL,17,Flistening.
OL,26,@oD@POUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778505069
OL,3,CBirmingham MP says Starmer must go as
OL,4,CPM fights off leadership pressure
OL,6,F"In the final hours of polling, many
OL,7,Fresidents on the doorstep expressed
OL,8,Funcertainty about their voting
OL,9,Fintention. Others were more direct.
OL,10,FThat hesitation was, in effect, a
OL,11,Fsignal of dissatisfaction with both
OL,12,Fthe speed of change and the leadership
OL,13,Fof that change within the Labour
OL,14,FParty."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@GO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778505069
OL,3,CBirmingham MP says Starmer must go as
OL,4,CPM fights off leadership pressure
OL,6,FShe added: "The results in Birmingham
OL,7,Fand across the country reflect that
OL,8,Fsentiment unequivocally. We saw paper
OL,9,Fcandidates ` who had done little in
OL,10,Fthe area and had no real understanding
OL,11,Fof the role ` elected, while excellent
OL,12,Fcandidates who would have served their
OL,13,Fcommunities well were lost.
OL,15,F"This election was fought and won on
OL,16,Fnational issues, over which local
OL,17,Fcouncillors had no control.
OL,19,F"Change now must come from the top."
OL,26,@nD@LOUwD@AOU{D@AOU{D@dO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
